Some  assorted  new stuff,  with one or two bits  of  pro-Asciilum 
propaganda mixed in as well - CiH..

A  joint venture by Apple,  Mitsubushi and the  toy  manufacturer 
Bandai are  releasing  in the USA a  complete  multimedia  system 
called  PIPPIN  that  will  connect to  a  standard  TV.  It  was 
originally  planned to be released by Christmas but has been  put 
back to early 1996.

