The  huge database company ORACLE launches next year a  low  cost 
computer  (target  price less than 400) which  will  give  VIDEO 
access to the internet.

             -----======>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======-----

Atari  are  in the news again,  but unfortunately for  the  wrong 
reason  (when  will  they learn!!).  After much  hype  about  the 
Virtual  Reality consule they are producing it has been  released 
that  the company they were in partnership with  (called  Virtual 
Reality - strangely enough!) has fallen out with them BIG TIME.
There  will not now be a new consule and Virtual Reality  are  in 
discussions with another major player in the games market.


