Microsoft  boss BILL GATES has bought one of the  worlds  largest 
photo  collections totalling 16,000,000 images. He has  plans  to 
license them in the form of software and online.

             -----======>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======-----

SUPER STARIOLAND is one of the success stories of the summer. The 
game  by TOP BYTE SOFTWARE has taken off in a big way with orders 
well in excess of those anticipated.  Great reviews by the glossy 
mags have helped and word is  that ST FORMAT pleaded for a demo.
Starioland can be purchased from ASCIILUM PDL.

             -----=====>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======-----
 
One of the ST's best known diskmags has recently celebrated its 
5th birthday,  well done MAGGIE.  I hear that the editors  C.I.H. 
and FELICE may be writing guest articles for ST WORLD. Who knows, 
they may even become regulars?

             -----======>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======----- 

I  recently read an interview in the greatly  respected  American 
diskmag  A-ONLINE with Jeff Minter.  He stated that he  had  many 
more registrations for the incredible LLAMATRON from ST users than 
from  either the PC or AMIGA users.  His total registrations  was 
well in excess of 2000 (including mine!).

             -----======>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======-----

USA internet providers are gradually taking over UK net providers. 
EUNet  GB  have  already been taken  over  this  year,  UUNET  is 
currently negotiating for UNIPALM and NETCOM has plans to  expand 
into  the UK.  The UK firm DEMON intends to stay independant  and 
has just raised 5.5m to expand its service.

             -----======>>>>>>><*<>>>>>>>======-----

IMPACT UK,  the creators of the excellent value educational menus 
are now up to release number 15.  However FLINTSTONE of IMPACT UK 
is  so productive that by the time you read this he has  probably 
released yet another.  The educational disks are a good selection 
of all the best educational programs compacted onto disks to give 
good value for money. 

             -----======>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======-----

A couple of new diskmags have appeared for the ST in the last 
couple of months. The B.O.S. was a 2 disk effort for issue 1 with 
a nice shell and loads of articles, ST WORLD issue 1 was put 
together with TOMS and Intro Concept but word is that they are 
expecting a customised shell soon. All diskmags need support,(*) 
especially new ones, so if you want a copy of either or both 
you can order them by name from ASCIILUM PDL. 
   (*)Especially MAGGIE - Ed..)

