That  sick  and evil man FRED WEST who murdered all  those  young 
girls  deserved a fate worse than suicide - but his  name  seemed 
strangely familiar and I could not remember where I had heard  it 
before. Then it came to me!, it's the name of a small program for 
the Atari. Unbelievably someone has created a printer spooler and 
called  it FRED WEST.  For those who are sceptical of this  weird 
bit of info check out ST REVIEW, DEC '94 issue 34 as it was given 
away on the cover disk. Ain't life strange!!! 

             -----======>>>>>>><*><<<<<<<======----- 

Who  says games are dead on the Atari?  I was speaking  to  ROBIN 
KEEN of Desert Star Software,  the creators of HOLLYWOOD  HUSTLER 
the  other day and he tells me that there has been more  response 
from the Atari platform than either the Amiga or PC.

